The article discusses the significance of Cinco de Mayo in American culture. It explains that on May 5, 1862, Mexican forces, led by General Ignacio Zaragoza, successfully defended against the invading army of Napoleon III at the Battle of Puebla. Despite being outnumbered, the Mexican soldiers displayed bravery and proved their commitment to Mexico's liberty and self-government. The article also mentions the celebration of Cinco de Mayo as a way to honor the heritage of Mexican Americans and their contributions to the United States. The author, presumably President Donald Trump, extends his best wishes for an enjoyable Cinco de Mayo celebration.